[
    {
        "content": "<p>Say I have <code>def MyNat := nat</code>. Is there a macro that will derive instsances for e.g. <code>has_add</code> from the <code>nat</code> instance?</p>",
        "id": 280273010,
        "sender_full_name": "Bernd Losert",
        "timestamp": 1651007543
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>@[derive has_add] def MyNat := nat</code></p>",
        "id": 280273069,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1651007587
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks. If I just want <code>MyNat</code> to be an \"alias\" to <code>nat</code>, how do I define it?</p>",
        "id": 280274158,
        "sender_full_name": "Bernd Losert",
        "timestamp": 1651008147
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Should I just define it as <code>syntax</code>?</p>",
        "id": 280274204,
        "sender_full_name": "Bernd Losert",
        "timestamp": 1651008176
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>abbreviation MyNat := nat</code></p>",
        "id": 280274470,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1651008339
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Cool. Thanks.</p>",
        "id": 280275533,
        "sender_full_name": "Bernd Losert",
        "timestamp": 1651008931
    }
]